<!-- Modal 2 - About -->
<div class="modal fade" id="aboutModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">On Camera: The Watchmen</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">

        <p>For <em>The Watchmen</em> show at Torrance Art Museum, the <a href="http://mobileartsplatform.wordpress.com/">Mobile Arts Platform</a> (MAP) will utilize their mobile printmaking backpack to hike a route through the city of LA and set up printmaking stations at locations that are in obvious view of surveillance cameras.</p> 

        <p>The project will be an attempt to start a dialogue with community residents and the surveillance cameras that reside in these neighborhoods. MAP will engage the public in front of these cameras, challenging participants to consider and respond to the camera's gaze in their community. 

        <p>What message or messages would you convey to surveillance cameras in your neighborhood?</p> 

        <p>The project is an intervention of fair exchange in which the public gets a free interactive screenprint relevant to their community in exchange for their opinions about their neighborhoods and the outside third eye. In this one-sided dialogue, participants fill in their response and hold it up to the camera.</p>

        <p>This project strives to provide a platform to consider community relationships to CCTV cameras while considering the concepts of audience and observer in our lives.</p> 

        <p>In collaboration with web designers <a href="http://www.nicocrisafulli.com">Nico Crisafulli</a> and <a href="http://bkahler.github.io/">Bryan Kahler</a>, MAP has created this interactive online map to provide a dialog space where the public can write in their thoughts using their smart phone or tablet.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
